sense.name: enumerate or arrange items in a series; be included in such series
sense.commentary: Note: Act of counting, ennumerating and arranging items into a list. Being included within a list, category, or classification.
sense.examples: I can list on one hand the times he has returned my calls. Let's see if we can list all the state capitals. She listed the things she needed to do. Glassware was listed on Mary's bridal registry at the store. She would like to be listed among the prominent socialites of Washington. He's listed among the founding members. She lists herself as a club member but never attends meetings.

sense.name: (cause to) physically tilt, lean over
sense.examples: The boat seems to be listing to port. The Titanic listed badly before finally sinking. Erosion listed the old tree.
